com.percussion.cms.objectstore
Class PSRelationshipFilter

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSRelationshipFilter

public class PSRelationshipFilter
extends Object

This class allows one to specify filtering criteria when querying for relationships by the implementer of the interface IPSRelationshipProcessor. The aim is to be able to specify the filtering conditions easily. The following rules apply when using the filter conditions.

  1. All specified conditions will be ANDed except for relationship name, type, and category. These 3 properties are OR'd together before they are AND'ed with the other properties. For example, if category and a property name-value is set, the results include the relationships that match the category and the property value. If the translation category and the Active Assembly Mandatory translation name are both specified, any relationship that is either AA mandatory or has a category of translation will be returned.
  2. The order of using filter parameters (if specified) will be as follows:
    1. relationship id
    2. relationship name
    3. relationship owner
    4. relationship dependent
    5. item contenttypeid
    6. item objecttypeid
    7. relationship category
    8. relationship type
    9. relationship properties

Author:
RammohanVangapalli

getCategory

public String getCategory()
Accessor for the relationship category filter.

Returns:
the name of the relationship category by which to filter, null or empty if not filtered by relationship category.
See Also:
setCategory(String)

setCategory

public void setCategory(String category)
Setter for the relationship category filter.

Note: if the category is FILTER_CATEGORY_FOLDER, then the name will be set to FILTER_NAME_FOLDER_CONTENT, since there is only one relationship type in folder category.

The category is OR'd with the name(s) and type(s) before AND'ing with the other properties.

Parameters:
category - the relationship category to be filtered by, null or empty to turn the relationship category filter off. Must be one of the FILTER_CATEGORY_XXX values defined in this class if not null or empty.

setType

public void setType(String type)
Setter for the relationship type filter.

The type is OR'd with the name(s) and category(ies) before AND'ing with the other properties.

Parameters:
type - the relationship type to be filtered by, null or empty to turn the relationship type filter off. Must be one of the FILTER_TYPE_XXX values defined in this class if not null or empty.

getNames

Returns:

setNames

public void setNames(Collection<String> names)
Limit the retrieved relationships to the supplied relationship names.

The name(s) are OR'd with the category(ies) and type(s) before AND'ing with the other properties.

Parameters:
names - the relationship names to be filtered by. Filter by name is off if it is empty or null. All white space characters will be stripped from the names since the space character is not allowed in the relationship name

setName

public void setName(String name)
Setter for the relationship name filter. This is used when filtered by only one relationship name.

Parameters:
name - the relationship name to be filtered by, null or empty to turn the relationship name filter off. Any name is allowed because the user can create his (or her) own relationships and may want to filter by the relationship name. However, all white space characters will be stripped from the name since the space character is not allowed in the relationship name.

getProperties

value - the property value to be filtered by. The filter for the property is turned off if the value is null or empty.

limitToEditOrCurrentOwnerRevision

public void limitToEditOrCurrentOwnerRevision(boolean limitToEditCurrOwnerRev)
The relationships are limited to the Edit Revision (if it exists) or the Current Revision (if Edit Revision does not exist) of the owner. This is typically used in conjunction with setDependent(PSLocator).

Note, this must not be used in conjuction with setDependentContentTypeId(long) or setDependentObjectType(int)

Parameters:
limitToEditCurrOwnerRev - true if the owner revision of the relationships are limited by Edit or Current revision as described above; otherwise the retrieved relationships may contain multiple owner revisions for a particular (dependent) item.

getLimitToEditOrCurrentOwnerRevision

public boolean getLimitToEditOrCurrentOwnerRevision()
Gets the filtered by Edit or Current revision of the owner of the retrieved relationships.

Returns:
true if the owner revision of the relationships are filtered by (or limited to) the Edit Revision (if it exists) or the Current Revision (if Edit Revision does not exist) of the owner; otherwise the retrieved relationships may contain multiple owner revisions for a particular (dependent) item. Defaults to false.
See Also:
limitToEditOrCurrentOwnerRevision(boolean)

toXml

public Element toXml(Document doc)
Serializes this object into XML form as specified in the following DTD: 
 <!ELEMENT PSXRelationshipFilter (Owner?, Dependents?, Properties?, TypeSet?)>
 <!ATTLIST PSXRelationshipFilter
     name CDATA #IMPLIED
     type CDATA #IMPLIED
     category CDATA #IMPLIED
     rid CDATA #IMPLIED
     communityFiltering CDATA #IMPLIED
 >
 <!ELEMENT Owner (PSXKey?)>
 <!ATTLIST Owner
     contenttypeid CDATA #IMPLIED
     objecttypeid CDATA #IMPLIED
 >
 <!ELEMENT Dependents (Dependent*, ContentTypeId*)>
 <!ELEMENT Dependent (PSXKey?)>
 <!ATTLIST Dependent
     contenttypeid CDATA #IMPLIED
     objecttypeid CDATA #IMPLIED
 >
 <!ELEMENT ContentTypeId (#PCDATA)>
 <!ELEMENT Properties (Property*)>
 <!ELEMENT Property EMPTY>
 <!ATTLIST Property
     name CDATA #REQUIRED
     value CDATA #REQUIRED
 >
 <!ELEMENT RelationshipNameSet (RelationshipName*)>
 <!ELEMENT RelationshipName EMPTY>
 <!ATTLIST RelationshipName
     name CDATA #REQUIRED
 >

Parameters:
doc - the XML document to be appended to, cannot be null
Returns:
the XML element that represents a PSRelationshipFilter. Never null.
